==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: aerialist
<hw>aer"i*al*ist</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>an athlete who
performs acts high above the ground on a trapeze or high wire, requiring
skill and agility and coordination.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> trapeze artist</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a burglar who gains entrance to buildings from the
rooftop, sometimes leaping from building to building in the process. A
type of <isa>second-story man</isa>.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aerial railway</ent>⟦br⟧
